snippet.textDisplay: Who wants to willingly buy Chinese tech though? I mean I understand if its some obscure product that has no real alternative but otherwise buying Chinese tech  is ill-advised at best. Guys I know this is a tech channel and they have to review and talk about all sorts of tech which is totally cool, but I would request you all to do some research on where your tech is coming from and how much control you really have over your tech. This is not to say non-Chinese brands are not violating your privacy but that Chinese are the worst offenders, I mean if possible buy phones that come with stock Android and as soon as the warranty (or even the day you get it) is over just insall AOSP Android or Linux and you get best of both world, modern performant hardware and some semblance of privacy.
